The paper focuses on using deep neural networks for software defect prediction, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The use of control flow graphs and multi-view multi-layer directed graph-based convolutional neural networks (DGCNNs) suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves compiling source code, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper deals with software defects, which could also fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
